{
  "video_id": "F5h6ynoq8uM",
  "title": "How to transform apocalypse fatigue into action on global warming | Per Espen Stoknes",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12760.0,
      "end_time": 16239.0,
      "text": "How do we get people engaged in solving global warming?"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 17440.0,
      "end_time": 21480.0,
      "text": "I&#39;d like to start with running two short experiments with you all."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 22560.0,
      "end_time": 27776.0,
      "text": "So your task is to notice if you feel any difference as I speak."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 27800.0,
      "end_time": 29000.0,
      "text": "OK?"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 30120.0,
      "end_time": 31320.0,
      "text": "Here we go."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 32200.000000000004,
      "end_time": 35416.0,
      "text": "We are seeing rising carbon dioxide levels,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 35440.0,
      "end_time": 37720.0,
      "text": "now about 410 ppms."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 38960.0,
      "end_time": 41816.0,
      "text": "To avoid the RCP 8.5 scenario,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 41840.0,
      "end_time": 44320.0,
      "text": "we need rapid decarbonization."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 45240.0,
      "end_time": 47296.0,
      "text": "The global carbon budget"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 47320.0,
      "end_time": 50816.0,
      "text": "for 66 percent likelihood to meet the two-degree target"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 50840.0,
      "end_time": 53480.0,
      "text": "is approximately 800 gigatons."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 55640.0,
      "end_time": 58176.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 58200.0,
      "end_time": 60440.0,
      "text": "OK, now let me try something else."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 61600.0,
      "end_time": 65640.0,
      "text": "We are heading for an uninhabitable earth:"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 66520.0,
      "end_time": 68616.0,
      "text": "monster storms,"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 68640.0,
      "end_time": 70376.0,
      "text": "killer floods,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 70400.0,
      "end_time": 72696.0,
      "text": "devastating wildfires,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 72720.0,
      "end_time": 76239.0,
      "text": "crazy heat waves that will cook us under a blazing sun."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 78840.0,
      "end_time": 82496.0,
      "text": "2017 is already so unexpectedly warm,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 82520.0,
      "end_time": 84816.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s freaking out climate scientists."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 84840.0,
      "end_time": 88776.0,
      "text": "We have a three-year window to cut emissions, three years."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 88800.0,
      "end_time": 92720.0,
      "text": "If not, we will soon live in a boiling earth, a hellhole."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 96000.0,
      "end_time": 98296.0,
      "text": "OK. So --"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 98320.0,
      "end_time": 99815.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 99840.0,
      "end_time": 101160.0,
      "text": "Now your task:"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 102600.0,
      "end_time": 105536.0,
      "text": "How did these ways of speaking make you feel?"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 105560.0,
      "end_time": 109656.0,
      "text": "The first, detached maybe or just confused?"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 109680.0,
      "end_time": 111109.0,
      "text": "What&#39;s this guy talking about?"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 112400.0,
      "end_time": 115360.0,
      "text": "The other, fearful or just numb?"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 116960.0,
      "end_time": 118455.0,
      "text": "So again, the question I asked:"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 118480.0,
      "end_time": 121976.0,
      "text": "How do we get people engaged in solving global warming?"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 122000.0,
      "end_time": 124680.0,
      "text": "And why don&#39;t these two ways of communicating work?"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 126000.0,
      "end_time": 130336.0,
      "text": "You see, the biggest obstacle to dealing with climate disruptions"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 130360.00000000001,
      "end_time": 131960.0,
      "text": "lies between your ears."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 133360.0,
      "end_time": 137336.0,
      "text": "Building on a rapidly growing body of psychology and social science,"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 137360.0,
      "end_time": 141336.0,
      "text": "I spent years looking into the five inner defenses"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 141360.0,
      "end_time": 143120.0,
      "text": "that stop people from engaging."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 143960.0,
      "end_time": 147616.0,
      "text": "When people hear news about the climate coming straight at them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 147640.0,
      "end_time": 150160.0,
      "text": "the first defense comes up rapidly:"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 151280.0,
      "end_time": 152480.0,
      "text": "distance."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 153400.0,
      "end_time": 154576.0,
      "text": "When we hear about the climate,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 154600.0,
      "end_time": 156696.0,
      "text": "we hear about something far away in space --"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 156720.0,
      "end_time": 159376.0,
      "text": "think Arctic ice, polar bears --"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 159400.0,
      "end_time": 161800.0,
      "text": "far away in time -- think 2100."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 163320.0,
      "end_time": 166880.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s huge and slow-moving -- think gigatons and centuries."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 168480.0,
      "end_time": 171440.0,
      "text": "So it&#39;s not here. It&#39;s not now."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 173000.0,
      "end_time": 174696.0,
      "text": "Since it feels so far away from me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 174720.0,
      "end_time": 177400.0,
      "text": "it seems outside my circle of influence,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 178520.0,
      "end_time": 180416.0,
      "text": "so I feel helpless about it."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 180440.0,
      "end_time": 181800.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s nothing I can do."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 183000.0,
      "end_time": 184416.0,
      "text": "In our everyday lives,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 184440.0,
      "end_time": 187296.0,
      "text": "most of us prefer to think about nearer things,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 187320.0,
      "end_time": 189536.0,
      "text": "such as our jobs, our kids,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 189560.0,
      "end_time": 192376.0,
      "text": "how many likes we get on Facebook."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 192400.0,
      "end_time": 194000.0,
      "text": "Now, that, that&#39;s real."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 196800.0,
      "end_time": 199000.0,
      "text": "Next defense is doom."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 200400.0,
      "end_time": 203160.0,
      "text": "Climate change is usually framed"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 203400.0,
      "end_time": 205960.0,
      "text": "as a looming disaster,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 205120.0,
      "end_time": 207896.0,
      "text": "bringing losses, cost and sacrifice."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 207920.0,
      "end_time": 209399.0,
      "text": "That makes us fearful."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 210240.0,
      "end_time": 213696.0,
      "text": "But after the first fear is gone,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 213720.0,
      "end_time": 217520.0,
      "text": "my brain soon wants to avoid this topic altogether."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 218360.0,
      "end_time": 221736.0,
      "text": "After 30 years of scary climate change communications,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 221760.0,
      "end_time": 226576.0,
      "text": "more than 80 percent of media articles still use disaster framings,"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 226600.0,
      "end_time": 229120.0,
      "text": "but people habituate to and then --"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 231160.0,
      "end_time": 232816.0,
      "text": "desensitize"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 232840.0,
      "end_time": 234336.0,
      "text": "to doom overuse."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 234360.0,
      "end_time": 237880.0,
      "text": "So many of us are now suffering a kind of apocalypse fatigue,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 239800.0,
      "end_time": 241840.0,
      "text": "getting numb from too much collapse porn."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 243760.0,
      "end_time": 246775.0,
      "text": "The third defense is dissonance."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 246800.0,
      "end_time": 249696.0,
      "text": "Now, if what we know,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 249720.0,
      "end_time": 252136.0,
      "text": "that fossil fuel use contributes to global warming,"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 252160.0,
      "end_time": 254856.0,
      "text": "conflicts with what we do -- drive, fly, eat beef --"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 254880.0,
      "end_time": 257200.0,
      "text": "then so-called cognitive dissonance sets in."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 258279.0,
      "end_time": 260176.0,
      "text": "This is felt as an inner discomfort."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 260200.0,
      "end_time": 261760.0,
      "text": "We may feel like hypocrites."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 262600.0,
      "end_time": 264160.0,
      "text": "To get rid of this discomfort,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 265000.0,
      "end_time": 268136.0,
      "text": "our brain starts coming up with justifications."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 268160.0,
      "end_time": 270176.0,
      "text": "So I can say, for instance,"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 270200.0,
      "end_time": 273000.0,
      "text": "\"My neighbor, he has a much bigger car than I do.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 274480.0,
      "end_time": 278296.0,
      "text": "Or, \"Changing my diet doesn&#39;t amount to anything"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 278320.0,
      "end_time": 280480.0,
      "text": "if I am the only one to do it.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 281720.0,
      "end_time": 285376.0,
      "text": "Or, I could even want to doubt climate science itself."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 285400.0,
      "end_time": 289390.0,
      "text": "I could say, \"You know, climate is always changing.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 291000.0,
      "end_time": 293936.0,
      "text": "So these justifications make us all feel better,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 293960.0,
      "end_time": 296575.0,
      "text": "but at the expense"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 296600.0,
      "end_time": 298696.0,
      "text": "of dismissing what we know."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 298720.0,
      "end_time": 302800.0,
      "text": "Thus, behavior drives attitudes."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 303920.0,
      "end_time": 306656.0,
      "text": "My personal cognitive dissonance comes up"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 306680.0,
      "end_time": 310160.0,
      "text": "when I recognize that I&#39;ve been flying from Oslo to New York"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 310400.0,
      "end_time": 311296.0,
      "text": "and back to Oslo"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 311320.0,
      "end_time": 314216.0,
      "text": "in order to speak about the climate."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 314240.0,
      "end_time": 315976.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 316000.0,
      "end_time": 317256.0,
      "text": "For 14 minutes."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 317280.0,
      "end_time": 321176.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 321200.0,
      "end_time": 323896.0,
      "text": "So that makes me want to move on to denial."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 323920.0,
      "end_time": 326176.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 326200.0,
      "end_time": 327976.0,
      "text": "So if we keep silent,"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 328000.0,
      "end_time": 332560.0,
      "text": "ignore or ridicule facts about climate disruptions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 332800.0,
      "end_time": 334895.0,
      "text": "then we might find inner refuge"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 334920.0,
      "end_time": 336360.0,
      "text": "from fear and guilt."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 337200.0,
      "end_time": 340896.0,
      "text": "Denial doesn&#39;t really come from lack of intelligence or knowledge."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 340920.0,
      "end_time": 344216.0,
      "text": "No, denial is a state of mind"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 344240.0,
      "end_time": 347960.0,
      "text": "in which I may be aware of some troubling knowledge,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 347120.0,
      "end_time": 349400.0,
      "text": "but I live and act as if I don&#39;t know."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 350560.0,
      "end_time": 352680.0,
      "text": "So you could call it a kind of double life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 353280.0,
      "end_time": 354775.0,
      "text": "both knowing and not knowing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 354800.0,
      "end_time": 357136.0,
      "text": "and often this is reinforced by others,"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 357160.0,
      "end_time": 358576.0,
      "text": "my family or community,"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 358600.0,
      "end_time": 361720.0,
      "text": "agreeing not to raise this tricky topic."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 363240.0,
      "end_time": 364920.0,
      "text": "Finally, identity."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 367440.0,
      "end_time": 369160.0,
      "text": "Alarmed climate activists"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 370680.0,
      "end_time": 372976.0,
      "text": "demand that government takes action,"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 373000.0,
      "end_time": 375696.0,
      "text": "either with regulation or carbon taxes."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 375720.0,
      "end_time": 377576.0,
      "text": "But consider what happens"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 377600.0,
      "end_time": 381336.0,
      "text": "when people who hold conservative values, for instance,"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 381360.0,
      "end_time": 385160.0,
      "text": "hear from an activist that government ought to expand even further."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 386760.0,
      "end_time": 388776.0,
      "text": "Particularly in rich Western democracies,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 388800.0,
      "end_time": 391720.0,
      "text": "they are then less likely to believe that science."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 393320.0,
      "end_time": 394656.0,
      "text": "How is that?"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 394680.0,
      "end_time": 398960.0,
      "text": "Well, if I hold conservative values, for instance,"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 398120.0,
      "end_time": 402856.0,
      "text": "I probably prefer big proper cars and small government"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 402880.0,
      "end_time": 405880.0,
      "text": "over tiny, tiny cars and huge government."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 407240.0,
      "end_time": 410616.0,
      "text": "And if climate science comes and then says"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 410640.0,
      "end_time": 412656.0,
      "text": "government should expand further,"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 412680.0,
      "end_time": 416440.0,
      "text": "then I probably will trust that science less."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 418320.0,
      "end_time": 420400.0,
      "text": "In this way, cultural identity"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 421320.0,
      "end_time": 423296.0,
      "text": "starts to override the facts."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 423320.0,
      "end_time": 425496.0,
      "text": "The values eat the facts,"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 425520.0,
      "end_time": 429359.0,
      "text": "and my identity trumps truth any day."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 431240.0,
      "end_time": 436256.0,
      "text": "So, after recognizing how these five D&#39;s kill engagement,"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 436280.0,
      "end_time": 437960.0,
      "text": "how can we move beyond them?"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 439240.0,
      "end_time": 442816.0,
      "text": "New research shows how we can flip these five defenses"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 442840.0,
      "end_time": 444976.0,
      "text": "over into key success criteria"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 445000.0,
      "end_time": 447440.0,
      "text": "for a more brain-friendly climate communication."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 448880.0,
      "end_time": 451976.0,
      "text": "So this is where it gets really exciting"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 452000.0,
      "end_time": 453840.0,
      "text": "and where we find the five S&#39;s,"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 455400.0,
      "end_time": 458920.0,
      "text": "the five evidence-based solutions for what does work."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 460120.0,
      "end_time": 462920.0,
      "text": "First, we can flip distance to social."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 463960.0,
      "end_time": 467416.0,
      "text": "We can make climate feel near, personal and urgent"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 467440.0,
      "end_time": 470496.0,
      "text": "by bringing it home,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 470520.0,
      "end_time": 473616.0,
      "text": "and we can do that by spreading social norms"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 473640.0,
      "end_time": 475776.0,
      "text": "that are positive to solutions."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 475800.0,
      "end_time": 478136.0,
      "text": "If I believe my friends or neighbors,"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 478160.0,
      "end_time": 479816.0,
      "text": "you guys, will do something,"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 479840.0,
      "end_time": 481390.0,
      "text": "then I will, too."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 482000.0,
      "end_time": 484840.0,
      "text": "We can see, for instance, this from rooftop solar panels."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 485360.0,
      "end_time": 488136.0,
      "text": "They are spreading from neighbor to neighbor like a virus."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 488160.0,
      "end_time": 489656.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s contagious."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 489680.0,
      "end_time": 493160.0,
      "text": "This is the power of peer-to-peer creating the new normal."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 494120.0,
      "end_time": 497200.0,
      "text": "Next, we can flip doom to supportive."
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 497800.0,
      "end_time": 499696.0,
      "text": "Rather than backfiring frames"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 499720.0,
      "end_time": 501760.0,
      "text": "such as disaster and cost,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 502720.0,
      "end_time": 506440.0,
      "text": "we can reframe climate as being really about human health,"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 508520.0,
      "end_time": 512535.0,
      "text": "for instance, with plant-based delicious burgers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 512558.99999999994,
      "end_time": 515255.99999999994,
      "text": "good for you and good for the climate."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 515280.0,
      "end_time": 518736.0,
      "text": "We can also reframe climate as being about new tech opportunities,"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 518760.0,
      "end_time": 521880.0,
      "text": "about safety and about new jobs."
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 523000.0,
      "end_time": 525616.0,
      "text": "Solar jobs, for instance, are seeing an amazing growth."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 525640.0,
      "end_time": 528199.0,
      "text": "They just passed the three million jobs mark."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 529440.0,
      "end_time": 532150.0,
      "text": "Psychology says, in order to create engagement,"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 532390.0,
      "end_time": 534616.0,
      "text": "we should present, on balance,"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 534640.0,
      "end_time": 538560.0,
      "text": "three positive or supportive framings"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 538800.0,
      "end_time": 539800.0,
      "text": "for each climate threat we mention."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 540680.0,
      "end_time": 542400.0,
      "text": "Then we can flip dissonance"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 543360.0,
      "end_time": 545496.0,
      "text": "to simpler actions."
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 545520.0,
      "end_time": 546976.0,
      "text": "This is often called nudging."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 547000.0,
      "end_time": 551360.0,
      "text": "The idea is, by better choice architecture,"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 552680.0,
      "end_time": 556496.0,
      "text": "we can make the climate-friendly behaviors"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 556520.0,
      "end_time": 558439.0,
      "text": "default and convenient."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 559480.0,
      "end_time": 561680.0,
      "text": "Let me illustrate this. Take food waste."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 562400.0,
      "end_time": 565816.0,
      "text": "Food waste at buffets goes way down"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 565840.0,
      "end_time": 569416.0,
      "text": "if the plate or the box size is reduced a little,"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 569440.0,
      "end_time": 572696.0,
      "text": "because on the smaller plate it looks full"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 572720.0,
      "end_time": 575416.0,
      "text": "but in the big box it looks half empty,"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 575440.0,
      "end_time": 576896.0,
      "text": "so we put more in."
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 576920.0,
      "end_time": 580455.0,
      "text": "So smaller plates make a big difference for food waste."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 580480.0,
      "end_time": 583176.0,
      "text": "And there are hundreds of smart nudges like this."
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 583200.0,
      "end_time": 587240.0,
      "text": "The point is, dissonance goes down as more behaviors are nudged."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 587840.0,
      "end_time": 591456.0,
      "text": "Then we can flip denial"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 591480.0,
      "end_time": 595176.0,
      "text": "by tailoring signals that visualize our progress."
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 595200.0,
      "end_time": 597616.0,
      "text": "We can provide motivating feedback"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 597640.0,
      "end_time": 599960.0,
      "text": "on how well we&#39;re doing with our problem-solving."
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 601000.0,
      "end_time": 603296.0,
      "text": "Say you improved your transport footprint"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 603320.0,
      "end_time": 605840.0,
      "text": "or cut energy waste in your buildings."
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 606480.0,
      "end_time": 609720.0,
      "text": "Then one app that can share this well is called Ducky."
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 610240.0,
      "end_time": 612176.0,
      "text": "The idea is, you log your actions there,"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 612200.0,
      "end_time": 616160.0,
      "text": "and then you can see how well your team or company is doing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 616400.0,
      "end_time": 617880.0,
      "text": "so you get real-time signals."
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 618720.0,
      "end_time": 620720.0,
      "text": "Finally, identity."
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 622120.0,
      "end_time": 624320.0,
      "text": "We can flip identity with better stories."
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 625520.0,
      "end_time": 627520.0,
      "text": "Our brain loves stories."
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 628880.0,
      "end_time": 631386.0,
      "text": "So we need better stories of where we all want to go,"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 631400.0,
      "end_time": 634216.0,
      "text": "and we need more stories of the heroes and heroines"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 634240.0,
      "end_time": 637640.0,
      "text": "of all stripes that are making real change happen."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 639560.0,
      "end_time": 643295.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m proud that my hometown of Oslo"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 643320.0,
      "end_time": 647656.0,
      "text": "is now embarking on a bold journey of electrifying all transport,"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 647680.0,
      "end_time": 650520.0,
      "text": "whether cars, bikes or buses."
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 651240.0,
      "end_time": 654120.0,
      "text": "One of the people spearheading this is Christina Bu."
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 654760.0,
      "end_time": 658496.0,
      "text": "She is heading the Electric Vehicle Association for years"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 658520.0,
      "end_time": 660536.0,
      "text": "and she has been fighting every day."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 660560.0,
      "end_time": 665550.0,
      "text": "Now, the UK and France, India and China have also announced plans"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 665800.0,
      "end_time": 667896.0,
      "text": "for ending the sales of fossil cars."
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 667920.0,
      "end_time": 669776.0,
      "text": "Now, that&#39;s massive."
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 669800.0,
      "end_time": 674776.0,
      "text": "And in Oslo, we can see how enthusiastic EV owners"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 674800.0,
      "end_time": 678256.0,
      "text": "go and tell their electric stories to friends and neighbors"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 678280.0,
      "end_time": 679576.0,
      "text": "and bring them along."
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 679600.0,
      "end_time": 683470.0,
      "text": "So we come full circle from story back to social."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 685520.0,
      "end_time": 688696.0,
      "text": "So thousands of climate communicators"
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 688720.0,
      "end_time": 691136.0,
      "text": "are now starting to use these solutions"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 691160.0,
      "end_time": 692360.0,
      "text": "all over the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 692800.0,
      "end_time": 696160.0,
      "text": "It is clear, however, that individual solutions"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 696400.0,
      "end_time": 698880.0,
      "text": "are not sufficient to solving climate alone,"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 699920.0,
      "end_time": 704680.0,
      "text": "but they do build stronger bottom-up support"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 706000.0,
      "end_time": 709216.0,
      "text": "for policies and solutions that can."
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 709240.0,
      "end_time": 712700.0,
      "text": "That is why engaging people is so crucial."
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 714120.0,
      "end_time": 716296.0,
      "text": "I started this talk"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 716320.0,
      "end_time": 719920.0,
      "text": "with testing two ways of communicating climate with you."
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 721720.0,
      "end_time": 723656.0,
      "text": "There is another way, too,"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 723680.0,
      "end_time": 725000.0,
      "text": "I&#39;d like to share with you."
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 725800.0,
      "end_time": 728536.0,
      "text": "It starts with reimagining climate itself"
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 728560.0,
      "end_time": 730319.0,
      "text": "as the living air."
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 731800.0,
      "end_time": 733976.0,
      "text": "Climate isn&#39;t really about some abstract, distant climate"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 734000.0,
      "end_time": 735256.0,
      "text": "far, far away from us."
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 735280.0,
      "end_time": 737800.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s about this air that surrounds us."
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 738720.0,
      "end_time": 741776.0,
      "text": "This air, you can feel in this room, too,"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 741800.0,
      "end_time": 744640.0,
      "text": "the air that moves right now in your nostrils."
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 745800.0,
      "end_time": 748479.0,
      "text": "This air is our earth&#39;s skin."
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 749320.0,
      "end_time": 751416.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s amazingly thin,"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 751440.0,
      "end_time": 756960.0,
      "text": "compared to the size of the earth and the cosmos it shields us from,"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 756120.0,
      "end_time": 758616.0,
      "text": "far thinner than the skin of an apple"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 758640.0,
      "end_time": 760560.0,
      "text": "compared to its diameter."
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 761840.0,
      "end_time": 763880.0,
      "text": "It may look infinite when we look up,"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 765280.0,
      "end_time": 770415.0,
      "text": "but the beautiful, breathable air is only like five to seven miles thin,"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 770440.0,
      "end_time": 774120.0,
      "text": "a fragile wrapping around a massive ball."
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 775640.0,
      "end_time": 777496.0,
      "text": "Inside this skin,"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 777520.0,
      "end_time": 779680.0,
      "text": "we&#39;re all closely connected."
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 780920.0,
      "end_time": 783336.0,
      "text": "The breath that you just took"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 783360.0,
      "end_time": 788960.0,
      "text": "contained around 400,000 of the same argon atoms"
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 788120.0,
      "end_time": 791120.0,
      "text": "that Gandhi breathed during his lifetime."
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 792960.0,
      "end_time": 796416.0,
      "text": "Inside this thin, fluctuating, unsettled film,"
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 796440.0,
      "end_time": 800240.0,
      "text": "all of life is nourished, protected and held."
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 801440.0,
      "end_time": 803376.0,
      "text": "It insulates and regulates temperatures"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 803400.0,
      "end_time": 807415.0,
      "text": "in a range that is just right for water and for life as we know it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 807440.0,
      "end_time": 810480.0,
      "text": "and mediating between the blue ocean and black eternity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 811440.0,
      "end_time": 814456.0,
      "text": "the clouds carry all the billions of tons of water"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 814480.0,
      "end_time": 815680.0,
      "text": "needed for the soils."
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 816480.0,
      "end_time": 819376.0,
      "text": "The air fills the rivers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 819400.0,
      "end_time": 821160.0,
      "text": "stirs the waters,"
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 821400.0,
      "end_time": 822240.0,
      "text": "waters the forests."
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 822920.0,
      "end_time": 825160.0,
      "text": "With a global weirding of the weather,"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 825400.0,
      "end_time": 829400.0,
      "text": "there are good reasons for feeling fear and despair,"
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 831120.0,
      "end_time": 836456.0,
      "text": "yet we may first grieve today&#39;s sorry state and losses"
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 836480.0,
      "end_time": 841200.0,
      "text": "and then turn to face the future with sober eyes and determination."
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 842640.0,
      "end_time": 844560.0,
      "text": "The new psychology of climate action"
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 845720.0,
      "end_time": 848536.0,
      "text": "lies in letting go, not of science,"
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 848560.0,
      "end_time": 851599.0,
      "text": "but of the crutches of abstractions and doomism,"
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 852600.0,
      "end_time": 854760.0,
      "text": "and then choosing to tell the new stories."
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 855640.0,
      "end_time": 857456.0,
      "text": "These are the stories"
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 857480.0,
      "end_time": 860816.0,
      "text": "of how we achieve drawdown, the reversing of global warming."
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 860840.0,
      "end_time": 863880.0,
      "text": "These are the stories of the steps we take"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 865800.0,
      "end_time": 868896.0,
      "text": "as peoples, cities, companies"
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 868920.0,
      "end_time": 870295.0,
      "text": "and public bodies"
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 870320.0,
      "end_time": 872216.0,
      "text": "in caring for the air"
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 872240.0,
      "end_time": 875400.0,
      "text": "in spite of strong headwinds."
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 876400.0,
      "end_time": 878136.0,
      "text": "These are the stories of the steps we take"
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 878160.0,
      "end_time": 881880.0,
      "text": "because they ground us in what we are as humans:"
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 882840.0,
      "end_time": 887360.0,
      "text": "earthlings inside this living air."
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 888640.0,
      "end_time": 889856.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 889880.0,
      "end_time": 893160.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}